// L5 store_data
WMemEn – 1 bit [31]; 1= we write to data memory, 0= we don't
WRegEn – 1 bit [30]; 1= we write to register, 0= we don't
Reg1 – 5 bits [29:25]; address of register 1 to read from (rt)
Reg2 – 5 bits [24:20]; address of register 2 to read from (rs)
WReg – 5 bits [19:15]; address of register to write to (rd)
Alu – 4 bits [14:11]; alu opcode like ADD (0000), SUB (0001), etc.
ALUSrc – 1 bit [10]; 1= we read the immediate as the 2nd ALU input, 0= we read reg2 as the 2nd ALU input
Branch – 1 bit [9]; 1 = we are branching, 0= we aren’t
BrType – 1 bit [8]; 1 = BLT, 0= not BLT
Imm – 8 bits [7:0]; immediate value; bottom 5 [4:0] is used as shift when ALUop = shift left/right

